[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing JavaBeans introspection**\n\nI notice that under native image, JavaBeans introspection may need metadata. However, I see there's a failure in the `:test` phase when running the command `gradlew nativeTest`. It appears that in the GraalVM plugin context, `nativeTest` usually runs the regular `test` first (which is on the JVM) before proceeding to `nativeCompile` and `nativeTest`. It's interesting to ponder the sequence and how that might impact the outcome!\n\n**Figuring out class names**\n\nI think there might be an issue with using nested class names that include a `$`. However, I can still use `ConfigurableErrorHandler.class.getName()`, since it contains a `$` in the string but is perfectly fine for class or file names. I remember that the rule states there shouldn't be a `$` in test class or file names. I shouldn't use reflection directly; instead, the public API requires the class name, but using `.class.getName()` seems acceptable.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08a982de9bcae927016a3e927387a481979a2e1f20287fc1d0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPpKOnSoF-ye7SlnSo3oQuPGnn7SL1ILtKxH6Rm-NMYl5_MqPxO_YaXFeLjsgn-_vMWsn2r3BCdyBXPTKjpyuJMXEId2Qdt-HEWtFV1C-onfSN5d8qOjcpQauqxQD7k6JSdjaGCLRdGbWHjWX4VCFp-KzDbdOfeXPeGqDB-rNN3sojWANekWa8nKb-k1dn4xwjKBqfwU3Es8iuPDpU0pZzisZHP98MYzos13X-FezcPOSXE0lRlodmpafIrKkGfTcb4WHvLFcfWiO5xmWR6YU5Psox-XWQoOKnzV6SIlp-ok_SKOeUIuid2S4zrT4S_EiqdbIRZ8wTw5KfsVJxMhAOpteXY8G8_lVGyrSWKUxVuQQrVci1bPGqkZYZdCnq1DNtC6DOdTZrEB9ui5s6PICkeCUoXmxt494agk1pM0G4mqG-nhe14gn8GJKFmEgMUq5zhm0uTOF2B7EMiGmB0XE0iYWKcOTbZLIgmv4r1dfnbjGLq60fnWqKTpbLCl4_nUPzMmFrPK2Sej60uwAjMOuiAVOi_7OLQ1tOo3EmQpr38RkHOIHcfCadrKyU-xKv8l23L8m-NO4f9gPJ1BLr45BlVMrwBmM_B8byNyZX5LMKb91cI6Rld-RfjBGcDUznRzsrr3PZe9TqCk9GmCM0j3FRfoejmDOemd42pScFDn7uSV0PoCj4Y4PHLvKyaEYY_tdxS0hDEghWUrxba5q8RBOMsHKhZHTjPklW-xsXXERaC7-5LjY8INi6xQn2kV2wVCGN-