. I remember that the rule states there shouldn't be a `$` in test class or file names. I shouldn't use reflection directly; instead, the public API requires the class name, but using `.class.getName()` seems acceptable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5bma4VzGBvAzxpdtczBZwQgU|fc_08a982de9bcae927016a3e928e35348197ae009423aae6b573", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-1.2-api/2.18.0/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_1_2_api/PropertySetterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.log4j.Level;\nimport org.apache.log4j.Priority;\nimport org.apache.log4j.config.PropertySetter;", "newText": "import org.apache.log4j.Appender;\nimport org.apache.log4j.Logger;\nimport org.apache.log4j.config.PropertySetter;\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.ErrorHandler;\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.LoggingEvent;"}, {"oldText": "        setter.setProperty(\"enabled\", \"true\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"threshold\", \"ERROR\");", "newText": "        setter.setProperty(\"enabled\", \"true\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"errorHandler\", RecordingErrorHandler.class.getName());"}, {"oldText": "        assertThat(target.isEnabled()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(target.getThreshold()).isEqualTo(Level.ERROR);", "newText": "        assertThat(target.isEnabled()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(target.getErrorHandler()).isInstanceOf(RecordingErrorHandler.class);"}, {"oldText": "        private boolean enabled;\n        private Priority threshold;", "newText": "        private boolean enabled;\n        private ErrorHandler errorHandler;"}, {"oldText": "        public Priority getThreshold() {\n            return threshold;\n        }\n\n        public void setThreshold(Priority threshold) {\n            this.threshold = threshold;\n        }", "newText": "        public ErrorHandler getErrorHandler() {\n            return errorHandler;\n        }\n\n        public void setErrorHandler(ErrorHandler errorHandler) {\n            