sure to keep everything current. ConfigurableTarget implements `OptionHandler`, which seems fine. I should also add an activated flag and figure out the key handling based on prefix length. Although the order of setting properties isn’t guaranteed, I think that’s okay, so I’ll proceed with editing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ame9Hq0KqHs6VUgPDMnYAIV8|fc_08a982de9bcae927016a3e92ee4a4881979b11d3eb0466e7b6", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-1.2-api/2.18.0/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_1_2_api/PropertySetterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.log4j.Appender;\nimport org.apache.log4j.Logger;\nimport org.apache.log4j.config.PropertySetter;\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.ErrorHandler;\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.LoggingEvent;", "newText": "import java.util.Properties;\n\nimport org.apache.log4j.config.PropertySetter;\nimport org.apache.log4j.spi.OptionHandler;"}, {"oldText": "        ConfigurableTarget target = new ConfigurableTarget();\n        PropertySetter setter = new PropertySetter(target);\n\n        setter.setProperty(\"name\", \"example-appender\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"count\", \"42\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"timeout\", \"123456789\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"enabled\", \"true\");\n        setter.setProperty(\"errorHandler\", RecordingErrorHandler.class.getName());", "newText": "        Properties properties = new Properties();\n        properties.setProperty(\"target.name\", \"example-appender\");\n        properties.setProperty(\"target.count\", \"42\");\n        properties.setProperty(\"target.timeout\", \"123456789\");\n        properties.setProperty(\"target.enabled\", \"true\");\n\n        ConfigurableTarget target = new ConfigurableTarget();\n        PropertySetter.setProperties(target, properties, \"target.\");"}, {"oldText": "        assertThat(target.isEnabled()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(target.getErrorHandler()).isInstanceOf(RecordingErrorHandler.class);", "newText": "        assertThat(target.isEnabled()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(target.isActivated()).isTrue();"}, {"oldText": "    public static final class ConfigurableTarget {\n\n        private String name;\n        private int count;\n        private long timeout;\n        private boolean enabled;\n        private ErrorHandler errorHandler;", "newText": "    public static final class ConfigurableTarget implements OptionHandler {\n\n        private String name;\n        private int count;\n        private long timeout;\n        private boolean enabled;\n        private boolean activated;"}, {"oldText": "        public ErrorHandler getErrorHandler() {\n            return errorHandler;\n        }\n\n        public void setErrorHandler(ErrorHandler errorHandler) {\n            this.errorHandler = errorHandler;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class RecordingErrorHandler implements ErrorHandler {\n\n        @Override\n        public void setLogger(Logger logger) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void error(String message, Exception exception, int errorCode) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void error(String message) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void error(String message, Exception exception, int errorCode, LoggingEvent event) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setAppender(Appender appender) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void setBackupAppender(Appender appender) {\n        }\n    }\n}", "newText": "        public boolean isActivated() {\n            return activated;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void activateOptions() {\n            activated = true;\n        }\n    }\n}"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 551, "output": 1676, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43187, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}},